LIST NETWORK INTERFACES : ip a s OR ip addr show

LISTEN ON ALL AVAILABLE INTERFACES : sudo tcpdump -i any

LISTEN ON SPECIFIC INTERFACE : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName

CAPTURE AND SAVE PACKETS IN FILE : sudo tcpdump -w FileName.pcap

READ ABOVE FILE : sudo tcpdump -r FileName.pcap

CAPTURE N PACKETS : sudo tcpdump -c N -i InterfaceName

AVOID IP RESOLUTION : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName -n

AVOID IP AND PORT NUMBER RESOLUTION : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName -nn

GET VERBOSE OUTPUT : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName -v

GET MANUAL : man tcpdump


CAPTURE ONLY FROM SPECIFIC HOST : 
    
    sudo tcpdump host IP -w FileName.pcap
    sudo tcpdump host HostName -w FileName.pcap

LIMIT PACKETS FROM SOURCE : 

    sudo tcpdump src host IP -w FileName.pcap
    sudo tcpdump src host HostName -w FileName.pcap

LIMIT PACKETS TO DESTINATION : 

    sudo tcpdump dst host IP -w FileName.pcap
    sudo tcpdump dst host HostName -w FileName.pcap

CAPTURE FROM SPECIFIC PORT : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName port PORT_NUM 

LIMIT FROM SPECIFIC PORT : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName src port PORT_NUM 

LIMIT TO SPECIFIC PORT : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName dst port PORT_NUM 

FILTER BY PROTOCOL : sudo tcpdump -i InterfaceName icmp OR ip OR ip6 OR udp OR tcp


LOGICL OPERATORS : and or not


FILTER PACKETS OF GREATER/LESS THAN EQUAL LENGTH : sudo tcpdump -r FileName.pcap less OR greater LEN

CAPTURE TCP ONLY SYNCRONIZE FLAG SET : sudo tcpdump "tcp[tcpflags] == tcp-syn"

    tcp-syn TCP SYN (Synchronize)
    tcp-ack TCP ACK (Acknowledge)
    tcp-fin TCP FIN (Finish)
    tcp-rst TCP RST (Reset)
    tcp-push TCP Push

CAPTURE ATLEAST SYNCRONIZE FLAG SET : sudo tcpdump "tcp[tcpflags] & tcp-syn != 0"

CAPTURE ATLEAST SYN OR ACK : sudo tcpdump "tcp[tcpflags] & (tcpsyn|tcp-ack) != 0"


tcpdump -q	Quick and quite: brief packet information
tcpdump -e	Include MAC addresses
tcpdump -A	Print packets as ASCII encoding
tcpdump -xx	Display packets in hexadecimal format
tcpdump -X	Show packets in both hexadecimal and ASCII formats
